                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.428/2068: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-02-18T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 18, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 18—11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>77. Foreign Office note received on the projected voyage of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Thorland</hi> to the Pacific halibut fishing grounds states: “It has now
                    been learned from the owners of the vessel that this project has been abandoned
                    for the current year.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
